a few questions?

24:15.300 --> 24:16.300
I'm innocent.

24:16.650 --> 24:18.850
Do you, uh,
recognize this?

24:19.650 --> 24:21.250
I see all kind of boxes, son.

24:22.250 --> 24:24.600
How about this guy?
Do you recognize him?

24:28.850 --> 24:30.100
I see what you driving at.

24:31.700 --> 24:34.000
This fellow brought a busted
cylinder head in here

24:34.050 --> 24:35.050
in that box, to be fixed.

24:35.800 --> 24:37.150
One of them get-
the-job-half-done-

24:37.200 --> 24:39.200
then-bring-it-in-here-for-
me-to-fix-it kind of guys.

24:39.300 --> 24:40.100
You know the type?

24:40.500 --> 24:41.950
Thinks he good with tools.

24:42.050 --> 24:44.700
Hopeless.
Like a woman.

24:44.750 --> 24:46.750
Worse than a woman,
a woman you might expect...

24:46.800 --> 24:48.850
Do you remember what you did
with the box?

24:49.850 --> 24:52.150
I took the part, he
tossed the box outside.

24:53.000 --> 24:54.500
I got the paperwork
inside.

25:04.450 --> 25:05.650
He came in
last Thursday.

25:05.900 --> 25:08.900
Guy's name is, uh...
Dean James.

25:09.200 --> 25:11.450
Hey, that's like, uh,
like James Dean...

25:11.500 --> 25:12.500
Only it's backwards.

25:12.550 --> 25:13.850
Yeah, right, we know.
Thanks, man.

25:15.150 --> 25:17.150
Okay, yeah, I didn't throw
the box out.

25:17.200 --> 25:19.850
I used it to take an engine part
to my mechanic. Okay?

25:20.050 --> 25:20.900
Why did you lie, Leo?

25:20.950 --> 25:22.700
Because I saw the thing
on the TV.

25:23.200 --> 25:25.500
It was you, in fact, saying
about how they found

25:25.550 --> 25:26.650
that dead kid out back there,

25:26.700 --> 25:27.650
and I-I thought you wouldn't
believe me

25:27.700 --> 25:29.600
if I told you I took the box
so close to the scene.

25:30.150 --> 25:30.950
You lied to us, Leo,

25:31.000 --> 25:33.700
and now you're changing
your story... again.

25:33.900 --> 25:35.500
What is it with you
and the truth, Leo?

25:36.100 --> 25:38.050
Look, I swear to God...

25:38.100 --> 25:39.950
And now we have both you
and the box

25:40.000 --> 25:41.600
within a hundred yards
of the scene

25:41.650 --> 25:43.500
on the night it happened.

25:44.250 --> 25:45.650
How do you think
that makes us feel?

25:46.200 --> 25:48.450
I... I used it
to take a part in.

25:49.200 --> 25:50.400
Talk to my mechanic.

25:50.650 --> 25:51.450
He'll tell you.

25:51.700 --> 25:52.650
We already have.

25:52.700 --> 25:54.800
So... what?
You think I...

25:55.250 --> 25:56.950
You think I brought the part in
and then...

25:57.400 --> 25:59.300
came back later and put
the little girl in the box?

25:59.350 --> 26:00.150
Does that make sense to you?

26:00.400 --> 26:02.600
What makes sense to me,
what doesn't make sense to me

26:02.650 --> 26:03.900
is none of your business.

26:04.700 --> 26:05.700
But I will tell you this:

26:05.900 --> 26:06.850
Every time I turn around,

26:07.150 --> 26:08.950
you get closer and closer
to the scene.

26:09.600 --> 26:10.700
Why is that, Leo?

26:11.000 --> 26:12.100
I don't know.

26:13.050 --> 26:13.850
Coincidence?

26:14.800 --> 26:16.200
So what's it going to be
next time?

26:18.550 --> 26:20.100
That... no,
that's the whole story.

26:20.150 --> 26:21.450
There's not going to be
a next time.

26:26.300 --> 26:29.050
Las Vegas police have exhausted
the few leads

26:29.100 --> 26:32.200
they had in the tragic case
of Baby Cordelia Doe;

26:32.350 --> 26:35.100
yet her identity and the
circumstances of her death

26:35.300 --> 26:36.350
remain a mystery.

26:36.750 --> 26:38.300
But desperate to find out
who she is

26:38.650 --> 26:41.900
and who killed her, forensic
experts have reconstructed

26:41.950 --> 26:43.450
the little girl's appearance

26:43.600 --> 26:45.950
as she would've looked
before she was murdered

26:46.000 --> 26:47.500
and left for dead.

26:48.100 --> 26:50.200
They're hoping the image
will look enough

26:50.300 --> 26:53.100
like the real girl to shake
loose someone's memory...

26:53.800 --> 26:54.600
That's my baby!

27:09.100 --> 27:11.900
That's my daughter!
That's my daughter!

27:12.000 --> 27:12.800
Get back!

27:25.500 --> 27:26.450
That's Inez.

27:27.700 --> 27:30.300
That is-is... my little girl.

27:32.750 --> 27:34.400
I wasn't there
to protect her.

27:36.550 --> 27:39.000
You guys put her
in the ground yet?

27:40.600 --> 27:41.400
Not yet.

27:41.600 --> 27:43.500
I would like to go
to the funeral.

27:44.500 --> 27:46.500
We might be able to arrange that.
Yeah.

27:50.100 --> 27:52.600
Do you know anyone
who wanted to harm her?

27:53.700 --> 27:56.350
Yeah... I know exactly
who did it.

27:57.100 --> 28:00.150
<i>It's the guy I used to share
my cell with-- Boyd Waldrip.</i>

28:00.550 --> 28:04.950
<i>I told him about my wife Grace,
what a good woman she was</i>

28:05.000 --> 28:08.400
<i>and how lucky I was
to have her.</i>

28:09.950 --> 28:11.050
<i>When Boyd got out,</i>

28:12.050 --> 28:15.850
I asked him to look
in on Grace and Inez...

28:17.000 --> 28:19.400
to take care of them
if they needed anything.

28:20.650 --> 28:22.100
He took care
of her all right.

28:22.750 --> 28:24.500
The bitch filed for divorce,
and...

28:24.750 --> 28:26.050
then she married Boyd.

28:28.600 --> 28:30.600
How could I have been so stupid?

28:31.700 --> 28:34.050
He killed Inez.

28:34.100 --> 28:35.150
He killed...

28:36.650 --> 28:38.400
my little baby girl. He...

28:40.500 --> 28:41.600
Why would he do that?

28:42.100 --> 28:42.900
I don't know.

28:42.950 --> 28:46.550
Maybe he did not want my face
staring up at him

28:46.700 --> 28:50.600
every morning, reminding him
what a piece of crap he was.

28:50.950 --> 28:51.900
Well, if he killed
your daughter,

28:51.950 --> 28:53.450
why didn't your wife
come forward?

28:54.000 --> 28:56.200
Maybe she's... dead, too.

28:57.300 --> 28:59.000
Maybe he killed her, too.

29:01.300 --> 29:04.100
When, uh, you guys
find him,

29:04.150 --> 29:05.500
will you send him
back down here?

29:05.550 --> 29:08.350
And then we'll save the state
a lot of money on him.

29:21.350 --> 29:22.650
LVPD! Open up!

29:27.800 --> 29:28.900
Clear!
Clear!

29:31.200 --> 29:33.550
Attention all officers,
attempt to locate white male,

29:33.850 --> 29:36.950
Boyd Waldrip, possibly
in the company of his wife,

29:37.000 --> 29:38.850
white female, Grace Waldrip

29:39.100 --> 29:41.650
and/or two young children,
descriptions to follow.

29:42.250 --> 29:45.300
Suspect's vehicle of record is
a yellow '78 Mercury Zephyr.

29:45.350 --> 29:49.200
Nevada tags: Zebra, George,
Nora, Paul, Three, Nine, Zero...

29:57.850 --> 30:00.950
Apparently when Waldrip got out,
he gained custody

30:01.000 --> 30:02.650
of his two kids
from a former marriage.

30:03.500 --> 30:06.100
First wife died of hepatitis
while he was inside.

30:06.500 --> 30:08.200
Maybe Inez's mother dyed
her hair

30:08.250 --> 30:11.000
so she'd fit in better
with her new siblings.

30:11.300 --> 30:12.700
Or else she was trying to make

30:12.750 --> 30:14.150
Inez look less like
her real father?

30:15.150 --> 30:16.300
To protect her?

30:20.850 --> 30:23.800
TV's still on, food
left on the table.

30:24.050 --> 30:25.150
They left in a hurry.

31:26.850 --> 31:28.250
<i>Tonight we have
new developments</i>

31:28.300 --> 31:30.550
<i>in the tragic death
of Inez Balboa,</i>

31:30.650 --> 31:31.700
<i>the child we've come to know</i>

31:31.750 --> 31:33.200
as Baby Cordelia Doe.

31:33.550 --> 31:36.800
Authorities are currently
engaged in a statewide manhunt

31:36.850 --> 31:39.000
for the child's mother
and stepfather...

31:39.200 --> 31:40.550
???

31:40.600 --> 31:41.400
If they're traveling
with their kids,

31:41.450 --> 31:42.450
they might be looking
for a place

31:42.500 --> 31:43.500
to leave them for awhile.

31:43.600 --> 31:45.650
Well, Waldrip has a sister
in Modesto,

31:45.950 --> 31:47.600
and Grace's mother lives
in Salt Lake City.

31:47.700 --> 31:49.550
We staked out both
of their residences.

31:50.150 --> 31:52.950
NHP is patrolling all the major
roads leading to them.

31:53.050 --> 31:53.850
Hold on a minute.

31:54.150 --> 31:55.050
Brass.

31:56.300 --> 31:57.200
I'm on my way.

31:58.500 --> 31:59.400
We got 'em.

32:12.300 --> 32:13.250
Boyd, listen!

32:14.150 --> 32:15.700
Let's find a way out of this.

32:16.850 --> 32:19.250
We've got to deal with the
safety of your kids first.

32:19.900 --> 32:21.300
We got
a hostage situation.

32:21.350 --> 32:22.900
A customer ID'd 'em
in there eating.

32:22.950 --> 32:23.750
They called the locals,

32:23.800 --> 32:26.300
but he burned us  and opened fire.
Anybody hit?

32:26.350 --> 32:28.450
I'm not sure. We got him
locked down there

32:28.500 --> 32:29.900
with his family
and some customers.

32:29.950 --> 32:31.550
How many inside?
I don't know.

32:32.000 --> 32:34.200
Nobody's been hurt yet;
nobody's gonna get hurt.

32:34.250 --> 32:35.400
That's the idea.

32:36.000 --> 32:38.400
That's the most important thing
right now, okay?

32:40.700 --> 32:42.050
Raise that camera higher.

32:48.750 --> 32:50.250
So why don't you work
with me here?

32:51.400 --> 32:53.000
Let's ease the kids out of this.

32:55.900 --> 32:56.700
Okay!

32:57.400 --> 32:58.750
Okay, I'm going to let
the kids out.

32:58.800 --> 32:59.650
Just put your weapons down.

33:00.000 --> 33:01.100
You got it, Boyd.

33:01.250 --> 33:02.050
Nice and easy.

33:04.250 --> 33:06.200
You're all right.
You're okay.

33:11.300 --> 33:12.100
Go.

