waiting for Grace to get home.

37:30.500 --> 37:31.300
Where's your sister?

37:37.200 --> 37:38.000
Inez?

37:47.800 --> 37:49.200
<i>I went outside looking
for Grace,</i>

37:51.500 --> 37:52.400
but she had the car,

37:52.450 --> 37:53.850
she wasn't home from work yet.

37:59.000 --> 37:59.800
<i>I was scared.</i>

38:00.800 --> 38:01.800
<i>I didn't know what to do.</i>

38:05.100 --> 38:08.200
<i>So you're telling me that
you had your little girl</i>

38:08.250 --> 38:11.000
<i>in your arms
with her heart still beating,</i>

38:11.050 --> 38:13.100
<i>and you took the bus
to the hospital?</i>

38:13.700 --> 38:15.800
<i>I thought if I let her go,
she would die.</i>

38:17.150 --> 38:19.000
But she died anyway.

38:56.100 --> 38:57.750
If it was just an accident,

38:58.650 --> 38:59.900
why didn't you just report it?

39:03.750 --> 39:05.000
Look at who I am.

39:07.950 --> 39:10.450
If I reported her death,
who would have believed me, huh?

39:13.100 --> 39:13.800
At the very least,

39:13.850 --> 39:15.450
they would have taken
my children away from me,

39:15.500 --> 39:17.350
probably sent me back
to jail, too.

39:18.750 --> 39:20.050
What would the point
of that have been?

39:24.800 --> 39:26.550
She was dead, and...

39:28.250 --> 39:30.000
breaking up my family
and leaving my children

39:30.050 --> 39:31.750
without a daddy
wasn't gonna bring her back.

39:34.450 --> 39:35.250
So you ran?

39:38.650 --> 39:40.100
See how well that turned out.

39:53.100 --> 39:54.050
Catherine?

39:55.350 --> 39:56.250
